.TH TILEMAPSTUDIO 1 "2026-06-10" "tilemap-studio 4.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tilemapstudio \- tilemap editor for Game Boy, GBC, GBA, NES and SNES
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tilemapstudio
.RI [ tilemap-file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Tilemap Studio
is a graphical editor for the tilemaps used by retro game consoles. It opens
and saves tilemaps in the native VRAM formats of the Game Boy, Game Boy Color,
Game Boy Advance, Nintendo Entertainment System (Famicom) and Super NES
(Super Famicom), as well as the formats used by the Pokemon Game Boy and Game
Boy Advance games and several homebrew and decompilation projects.
.PP
It pairs a tileset image with a tilemap, supports per-tile palette, flip and
priority attributes, and edits maps of arbitrary size in a resizable, zoomable
canvas.
.PP
Tilemap Studio is a graphical (FLTK) application; it takes no command-line
options other than an optional tilemap file to open at startup. All editing is
done through the window's menus and toolbar.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I tilemap-file
Open the given tilemap file on startup.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.tilemap-studio.prefs
Per-user preferences, stored via FLTK's preferences mechanism.
